    "created_at": "2016-08-09T18:43:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-09T18:43:44Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Given that this is blocking [issue 7609](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/7609), I think we should have this discussion sooner rather than later.\n\nMaking an assessment of this now: I think either `grpcio` has to take a dependency on `oauth2client`, or there needs to be some kind of `grpcio-auth` package that depends on `oauth2client`. The key bit of code is [`grpc._auth.GoogleCallCredentials`](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/bdec15786226306fa56e15c7d95c389eb3d90810/src/python/grpcio/grpc/_auth.py#L43), which implements [a `grpcio` interface](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/bdec15786226306fa56e15c7d95c389eb3d90810/src/python/grpcio/grpc/__init__.py#L403) and takes an instance of [an `oauth2client` class](https://github.com/google/oauth2client/blob/2e8d1bea6464476d4e34801e59695adc95fd6b9e/oauth2client/client.py#L1064) as a construction parameter. I hoped there might be some way to tease them apart, so that on the `grpcio` side there could be a function that takes as a parameter a function that does-thus-and-such in neutral non-`oauth2client` non-`grpcio` terms and on the `oauth2client` side there could be a function that does-thus-and-such in neutral non-`oauth2client` non-`grpcio` terms, but I just don't see a way to thread the needle.\n\nAm I missing anything @jonparrott @dhermes @kpayson64 @soltanmm?\n"
  },
