    "created_at": "2016-11-03T18:04:06Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-03T18:04:06Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I agree that the dependency relationship should be _application_ → `google-auth-library-python` → `grpcio`. This means that `grpcio` will not add to its final API code elements like [`google_call_credentials`](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/aa3863b4b7e2f44d27a656caf98322389ac8a805/src/python/grpcio/grpc/beta/implementations.py#L53) that were present in its Beta API and that caused `grpcio` to depend upon `oauth2client`. It might also mean that [the code in `grpcio` implementing the `google_call_credentials` Beta API function](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/aa3863b4b7e2f44d27a656caf98322389ac8a805/src/python/grpcio/grpc/_auth.py#L43) would need to be relocated from `grpcio` to `google-auth-library-python` (this may have already happened, in effect if not in specifically described action).\n\nIs this assessment correct? Is this assessment agreeable to everyone in this conversation? (It's agreeable to me.)\n"
  },
