    "created_at": "2016-11-03T18:36:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-03T18:36:50Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I want to avoid keeping `google_call_credentials` because I want to avoid `grpcio` having code elements that \"point up\" the layers of abstraction/\"look back\" against the direction of dependency relationships (and I also want to avoid `grpcio` having conditional imports and the other trickery that goes along with that).\n\n\"`grpcio` and `google-auth-library-python` interdepend!\" would be live-withable but having the dependency unidirectional is preferable when delivering the exact same application-visible value.\n\n`google_call_credentials`, being in the Beta API, is already deprecated. I'm not yet aware of a reason to kill it sooner or later than the rest of the Beta API.\n\nOkay, [one reason](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/8621).\n"
  },
